{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`pi-vimmode` already has three related discovery surfaces: - `src/customization.ts` formats `:actions`, `:keymap`, `:mapcheck`, and `:vimdoctor` from resolved keymap/options metadata."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 11", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Add typed source-backed metadata for finite diagnostic/help action IDs such as `vimmode.doctor`, `vimmode.actions`, `vimmode.keymap`, `vimmode.mapcheck`, `vimmode.help`, `vimmode.features`, `vimmode.messages`, and `vimmode.inspect`."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision: Add a separate metadata-only diagnostic action registry Target seams: new small helper such as `src/diagnostic-actions.ts`, imported by `src/customization.ts`, `src/runtime-help.ts`, and docs-drift tests."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_decision_add_a_separate_metadata_only_diagnostic_action_registry", "label": "Decision: Add a separate metadata-only diagnostic action registry", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 30", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: new small helper such as `src/diagnostic-actions.ts`, imported by `src/customization.ts`, `src/runtime-help.ts`, and docs-drift tests. Each entry should carry a stable metadata ID, category (`diagnostic` or `runtimeHelp`), command/query terms, description, examples, docs/spec/test anchors, and `bindable: false`. Entries describe existing finite commands; they do not contain dispatch functions."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_decision_keep_bindability_as_a_type_config_boundary_not_a_runtime_convention", "label": "Decision: Keep bindability as a type/config boundary, not a runtime convention", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 42", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/prompt-transform-actions.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `src/types.ts`, and config tests. `piVimMode.keymap.actions` should continue to accept only `BindablePromptTransformActionId` (`prompt.transform.*`). Metadata-only IDs such as `vimmode.doctor` and aliases such as `promptTransform.reflow` should be rejected with warnings that preserve valid sibling entries. Diagnostic/help metadata can be searchable, but config must not treat it as dispatchable."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_decision_route_discovery_through_shared_metadata_while_preserving_current_command_scopes", "label": "Decision: Route discovery through shared metadata while preserving current command scopes", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 53", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `actionsMessage`, `searchActions`, `runtimeHelpMessage`, `runtimeFeaturesMessage`, `test/customization.test.ts`, and `test/runtime-help.test.ts`. `:actions` should remain an action/diagnostic search surface, not a general help browser. Its empty summary may include diagnostic/runtime-help counts or categories, and queries should find metadata IDs, command names, descriptions, and aliases. `:features` should keep broader feature lookup and effective runtime state reporting. `:help` "}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_decision_treat_quickref_classification_as_docs_plus_drift_guarded_metadata_not_neovim_parity", "label": "Decision: Treat quickref classification as docs plus drift-guarded metadata, not Neovim parity", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 64", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `docs/features.md`, `src/runtime-help.ts`/new metadata anchors, and `test/docs-drift.test.ts`. The quickref should group supported pi-vimmode surfaces by actual behavior: modal motions/edits, Ex line commands, prompt transforms, customization diagnostics, runtime help/inspectability, and keybindable prompt transform actions. It should explicitly exclude unsupported quickref/parity surfaces such as Vim help tags, `:map`, `:action`, plugin APIs, and diagnostic keybinding dispatch."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_decision_preserve_existing_read_only_side_effect_boundaries", "label": "Decision: Preserve existing read-only side-effect boundaries", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 75", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/ex.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts` if touched, plus modal tests. This change should not add parser branches or modal dispatch. If implementation touches execution to wire metadata messages, diagnostic/help commands must still preserve prompt text, cursor position, visual state, search highlights, registers, marks, macros, message-history rules, and dot-repeat except for existing transient/retained diagnostic message behavior. `:messages` must not ret"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 85", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Metadata duplicates command names already known by `src/ex.ts` \u2192 Mitigation: drift tests should assert metadata command names are accepted by parser where applicable and docs anchors exist. - `:actions` output becomes too dense for one-row feedback \u2192 Mitigation: keep empty summaries compact; query output returns one best match; long docs remain in `docs/features.md`. - Metadata-only IDs accidentally become bindable \u2192 Mitigation: keep diagnostic registry separate from `BindablePromptTransformAc"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 93", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add metadata-only diagnostic/help entries and unit tests for IDs, aliases, docs anchors, and `bindable: false` invariants. 2. Wire metadata into customization/runtime-help lookup and update focused tests for `:actions`, `:features`, and `:help` queries. 3. Extend docs-drift tests for metadata docs/spec/test anchors and quickref classification anchors."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_ref_src_customization_ts", "label": "customization.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_ref_src_runtime_help_ts", "label": "runtime-help.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 6", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_ref_src_prompt_transform_actions_ts", "label": "prompt-transform-actions.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_ref_src_diagnostic_actions_ts", "label": "diagnostic-actions.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-diagnostic-action-registry-quickref/design.md", "source_location": "line 32", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_diagnostic_action_registry_quickref_design_context